OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1778253065
OL,3,CChief Constable apologises again to
OL,4,CKatie Simpson's family
OL,6,FThe trial of Creswell, 36, for the
OL,7,Fmurder of Ms Simpson ended in April
OL,8,F2024 after he took his own life
OL,9,Ffollowing the first day of proceedings.
OL,11,FThe review led by Dr Jan Melia found
OL,12,Fthat "institutional misogyny" in the
OL,13,FPSNI contributed to "clear warning
OL,14,Fsigns" being missed in the original
OL,15,Finvestigation.
OL,17,FMr Boutcher said Ms Simpson was a
OL,18,F"bright, bubbly young woman with a
OL,19,Fbold sense of humour, a great work
OL,20,Fethic and a bright future ahead of
OL,21,Fher".
OL,26,@tD@FOUtD@]O]uD@UOUvD@FO]zD@AOU}D@DO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
